NOTE: We only show up to 90 since there're only 90 lines in this file.
Here's the result of running `cat -n` on /workspace/test_runner.sh:
     1	#!/bin/bash
     2	set -euo pipefail
     3	
     4	# Define tests: pairs of input and expected output (without trailing newline)
     5	inputs=(
     6	"3
     7	takahashi 2
     8	aoki 6
     9	snuke 5
    10	"
    11	"1
    12	abc 100
    13	"
    14	"3
    15	a 1
    16	ab 2
    17	aba 3
    18	"
    19	"4
    20	zz 10
    21	aa 20
    22	mm 30
    23	bb 40
    24	"
    25	"3
    26	alpha 1
    27	beta 2
    28	gamma 3
    29	"
    30	"5
    31	delta 1
    32	echo 2
    33	bravo 3
    34	charlie 4
    35	foxtrot 5
    36	"
    37	)
    38	
    39	expected=(
    40	"snuke"
    41	"abc"
    42	"aba"
    43	"zz"
    44	"alpha"
    45	"echo"
    46	)
    47	
    48	fail=0
    49	
    50	for i in "${!inputs[@]}"; do
    51	    inp="${inputs[$i]}"
    52	    exp="${expected[$i]}"
    53	
    54	    # Read N
    55	    N=$(printf "%s" "$inp" | sed -n '1p')
    56	
    57	    # Read the following N lines and collect names and ratings
    58	    total=0
    59	    names=()
    60	    while IFS= read -r name rating; do
    61	        # skip empty lines
    62	        if [ -z "$name" ]; then
    63	            continue
    64	        fi
    65	        names+=("$name")
    66	        total=$((total + rating))
    67	    done < <(printf "%s" "$inp" | sed -n '2,$p')
    68	
    69	    # Sort names lexicographically
    70	    IFS=$'\n' sorted=( $(printf "%s\n" "${names[@]}" | sort) )
    71	    unset IFS
    72	
    73	    idx=$(( total % N ))
    74	    winner="${sorted[$idx]}"
    75	
    76	    if [ "$winner" != "$exp" ]; then
    77	        echo "Test $((i+1)) failed"
    78	        echo "Input:"; printf "%s\n" "$inp"
    79	        echo "Expected: $exp"
    80	        echo "Got: $winner"
    81	        fail=1
    82	    fi
    83	done
    84	
    85	if [ "$fail" -eq 0 ]; then
    86	    echo "All tests passed"
    87	    exit 0
    88	else
    89	    exit 1
    90	fi
